    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter" xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Miklós Oláh to Cornelis De Schrijver (Brussels, 5 October
                    1536)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">He thanks him for the Erasmus of Rotterdam epitaph and
                            the Panagne. Some of his friends have also sent him the Erasmus epitaphs
                            they have written, and he has sent these to Cornelis De Schrijver along
                            with his own so he can correct his poem. He sends his regards to
                            Maximiliaan van Zevenbergen, and he will give Cornelis de Schepper the
                            book when he is back from Zeelandia. </p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Nicolaus Olaus Cornelio Grapheo salutem. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.2"
                    ><?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="255,255,0"?>[Quae tu
                        grandissimo…]<?oxy_custom_end?><note type="critic" xml:id="note.1"><hi
                            rend="smallcap">Ipolyi</hi> 1875, 589. In Romanian: <hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Capoianu–Costa–Nicolae</hi> 2022, 1406–1409.</note></p>
                <pb/>
                <p xml:id="p.3">Habeo praeterea tibi, mi Scriboni, gratias de epitaphio
                        <persName>Erasmi</persName> et <hi rend="italic">Panagne</hi><note
                        type="critic" xml:id="note.2">De Schrijver’s book <hi rend="italic">Ad
                            optimam heroidem Mariam</hi>… mentioned in Ep. 551. and Ep. 574. Part I:
                        Panagne, quae Virg. Mariae epithalamium, II: Theander, quae aureo mundo Dei
                        hominis nativitatem, II: Pan, qui veri Panos Christi necem canit. Praeter
                        alia quaedam piis affectibus plena… See also <hi rend="smallcap">Beer</hi>
                        1903, LXVII: “Corn. Graphei Panagne, h. e. rusticus in divi Joseph e Mariae
                        nuptias lusus. Med. 243. Corn. Grapheus descripsit senatum Antverpiae
                        civitatis a Carolo V. insitutum. Liber impressus Antverp. in 4° 1541: Conr.
                        Gesner, Bibliotheca univ., fol.
                        188.”<ref>olahus.tei.15351201_1</ref></note><ref>/o:olahus.tei.15360924_1</ref>
                    tua ad me missa,<note type="critic" xml:id="note.3">Ep.
                            574.<ref>olahus.tei.15360924_1</ref></note> ex qua cognosco iam
                    penitius, quam antea ingenii tui excellentiam. Quidam amici mei diebus
                    superioribus miserunt ad me quaedam Erasmi epitaphia ab eis conscripta,<note
                        type="critic" xml:id="note.4">See the epitaphs of Frans van Cranevelt: <hi
                            rend="smallcap">Ipolyi</hi> 1875, 581; and François de Bourgogne: <hi
                            rend="smallcap">Hegedüs</hi> 1906, 374; <hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Fógel–Juhász</hi> 1934, 4; <hi rend="smallcap">Neagu</hi> 2003, 294.
                        See also Cranevelt’s letter Ep. 571.<ref>olahus.tei.15360910_1</ref></note>
                    quae cum meis <del corresp="Olahus">rudibus</del> carminibus ad te misi, ut
                    illorum scripta videres, mea autem carmina, vere videlicet Transylvana vel
                    silvana potius, castigares. Carmen, quo tibi respondi, boni consule, veluti
                    extemporaneum. <persName>Maximilianum</persName><note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.5">Maximiliaan van Zevenbergen.</note> salutavi tuo nomine.
                        <persName>Cornelius <add corresp="Olahus" type="insert"
                        >Scepperus</add></persName> profectus est ante XVI. diem ad
                        <placeName>Selandiam</placeName>,<note type="critic" xml:id="note.6">See Ep.
                        572. Cap. 2.<ref>olahus.tei.15360916_1</ref></note> cui, cum redierit,
                    reddam libellum. Vale feliciter, mi Corneli, et me tuum esse existima habeque
                    commendatum. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.4"><placeName>Bruxellae</placeName> 5. Octobris 1536.</p>
            </div>
